ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.10.Live.PDTV.x264-NX

Monday 14th July 2014 ITV4
12:30pm to 5pm Live

Live coverage of stage 10 on Bastille Day and the French have devised a stage that is sure to produce some incredible fireworks at La Planche des Belles Filles. This is where Chris Froome took his first Tour de France stage win back in 2012 and following the same format, the route is a short but intense 161.5km over seven categorised climbs. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting the reporter at the roadside.
